{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RB91u4eNx1BgYpEeej2yvH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018q1wWPHPdfbYw9CTxwoD8A","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/examples-rererun/spark-spark_etl_skew_oom-20260623_122446/stages/stage_1/submit.txt","content":"ROOT CAUSE: Data skew in Stage 3 (GROUP BY user_id) — user_id 999 holds 50,000/100,000 records (50% of all data, skew ratio 500x). With only 256MB executor memory, the single partition containing all user_id=999 records caused OutOfMemoryError.\n\nDIAGNOSIS:\n- Diagnostic server confirmed: hot key user_id=999, skew_ratio=500x (>> 10x threshold)\n- skew_info.txt: total_records=100000, hot_user_records=50000, skew_ratio=500x\n- Stage 3 aggregation forces all 50k records into one executor partition → OOM at 256MB\n\nFIX APPLIED (etl-job.yaml):\n- Increased executor memory: --conf spark.executor.memory=1g (from 256m)\n- Enabled Adaptive Query Execution: --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n- Enabled AQE skew join handling: --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n\nAQE skewJoin splits oversized partitions at runtime, preventing a single executor from receiving the entire user_id=999 dataset. Combined with 1g executor memory, this eliminates the OOM.\n\nRESULT: ETL job (etl-job-dcc6r) completed successfully — all 3 stages passed, output: spark_etl_pipeline_verified\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2935,"cache_read_input_tokens":39276,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2935},"output_tokens":42,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed86dc7a-60c1-46b6-8fdb-aaf1099d6c0e","uuid":"77f7846f-6627-4e41-adde-1ac68848b160","request_id":"req_011CcLCFTYdTNwRWofzuwU9H"}
