{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011KrnnHsrzGeXkfdbvQRpTJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete diagnosis and resolution:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis: Data Skew OOM in Stage 3\n\n**Root Cause:** Severe data skew on `user_id 999`.\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Total records | 100,000 |\n| Records for user_id 999 | 50,000 (50%) |\n| Skew ratio | **500x** (threshold: >10x) |\n| Executor memory | 256MB (insufficient) |\n\nWhen Stage 3 executes `GROUP BY user_id`, Spark hashes all records for `user_id=999` into a single partition. That partition alone holds 50,000 records, overwhelming the 256MB executor memory → `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n---\n\n## Fix Applied (`etl-job.yaml`)\n\nThree changes to the `spark-submit` command:\n\n1. **Increase executor memory** — `--conf spark.executor.memory=1g`  \n   Gives each executor 4× the headroom to hold the skewed partition.\n\n2. **Enable AQE** — `--conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true`  \n   Turns on runtime query plan optimization.\n\n3. **Enable AQE skew join** — `--conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true`  \n   Automatically detects and **splits oversized partitions** at runtime, so no single executor receives the entire `user_id=999` dataset.\n\n---\n\n## Result\n\nThe ETL job (`etl-job-dcc6r`) completed successfully in 89 seconds:\n- All 3 stages passed\n- Final output: `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`\n- Job status: `Complete 1/1`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":702,"cache_read_input_tokens":42211,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":702},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed86dc7a-60c1-46b6-8fdb-aaf1099d6c0e","uuid":"bc530654-a695-4b91-9e03-51ce8bcbd803","request_id":"req_011